title: Teen Reels In Fish That's Bigger Than Him #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Tyler Robinson allegedly cracked jokes with his friends hours after he allegedly assassinated Charlie Kirk. In a group chat on Discord, a friend thought Robinson looked like the killer in photos released by the FBI. "My doppelganger is trying to get me in trouble," Robinson replied. "Whatever you do, don't go to McDonalds any time soon," the friend advised Robinson, in reference to the arrest of Luigi Mangione, the accused killer of UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson.
title: Several Similarities Between Tyler Robinson And Luigi Mangione

author: Inside Edition
description: When police responded to a disturbance call, they found another cop already there, but something didn't seem right. Police asked Michael Scaletta for his commission card but he failed to produce the card that would identify him as a police officer. Police in Washington, were certain Scaletta was impersonating a police officer, a crime happening more often these days. A background check confirmed Scaletta is a convicted felon. Scaletta has pled not guilty to impersonating a police officer.
title: Man Impersonating Police Officer Caught By Actual Cops

author: Inside Edition
description: Jaws dropped as Sydney Sweeney strode out on stage in a strapless red gown with a heart-shapped neckline at this year's Emmys. Her accessories came out to a total of 175 carats, including a 120-carat diamond necklace. The Emmy's is the first red carpet of awards season and the Hollywood fashion marathon, ending with the Oscars. The big names did not disappoint. CBS Mornings' Gayle King wore a jewel-tone gown, a trend of the night.
title: Red Carpet Looks That Stunned At This Year's Emmys

author: Inside Edition
description: Erika Kirk whispered her final goodbye to her slain husband in his casket. Charlie Kirk's widow also stood next to her late husband's empty chair in the studio where he recorded his popular podcast. She spoke about the heartbreaking moment she had to tell their 3-year-old daughter, Gigi, that her father was never coming back. Erika said she was taking on Charlie's political movement, Turning Point USA. Fate has pushed Erika into political prominence at a pivotal moment in America.
title: Charlie Kirk's Widow, Erika, Says Her Final Goodbye

author: Inside Edition
description: A national symbol of Australia, koalas are endangered. Experts say they could disappear from the earth as early as 2050. One thing causing their population decline is disease, specifically chlamydia. Now a vaccine has been approved to help them survive an infection. The Australian government has approved the vaccine to be administered by vets in hospitals, clinics, and the wild. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Vaccine Approved to Help Koalas Survive Chlamydia, Which Is Decimating Population

author: Inside Edition
description: In a new documentary called "Ruby & Jodi: A Cult of Sin and Influence," Investigation Discovery uncovers how Jodi Hildebrandt became the mastermind of the two mothers. Hildebrandt's niece, former victim Jessi Hildebrandt, shared their experience with Inside Edition's Alison Hall, who says their time with their aunt turned "abusive" and "torturous." They say they are "still dealing with the repercussions" today. ID’s Ruby & Jodi: A Cult of Sin and Influence is now streaming on HBO Max.
title: Jodi Hildebrandt's Niece Speaks Out About 'Torturous' Experience
